Saudi Arabia's first-ever fashion week has kicked off in the capital Riyadh as social restrictions ease in the ultra-conservative kingdom. Reuters' Emily Wither reports from the capital. The backstage nerves at any fashion show can be high - but this is Saudi Arabia, and these women will be the first to walk the catwalk at the country's first-ever fashion week. Read More: Black Panther To Become First Film To Be Shown In Saudi Arabia In 35 Years